article.description: Tevin Findlay had a perfect day shooting for 19 points and Khalil Small had 16, both career highs, and Green Bay rolled to a 108-57 win over Wisconsin-Superior on Sunday.
article.headline: Green Bay rolls to 108-57 win over D-III Superior
article.linkText: Green Bay rolls to 108-57 win over D-III Superior
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Tevin Findlay had a perfect day shooting for 19 points and Khalil Small had 16, both career highs, and Green Bay rolled to a 108-57 win over Wisconsin-Superior on Sunday. Carrington Love added 15 points for the Phoenix (6-4), which broke 100 for the first time in 10 years and shattered the school record with 22 steals. Findlay hit all seven field-goal attempts and four free throws as Green Bay shot 68 percent in the second half to score 65 points. Green Bay led 43-26 at halftime, limiting the Yellowjackets to 29 percent shooting and forcing 13 turnovers that were turned into 18 points. The Division-III Yellowjackets (4-5) missed their first 12 shots and were 2 of 12 to fall behind 25-9 as the Phoenix were making 12 of their first 17. Zach Schradle had 13 points for Superior, which had 27 turnovers and shot 33 percent.
